Subject: FLEA-2007-0040-1 thunderbird

-----BEGIN PGP SIGNED MESSAGE-----
Hash: SHA1

Foresight Linux Essential Advisory: 2007-0040-1
Published: 2007-08-03

Rating: Moderate

Updated Versions:
    thunderbird=/conary.rpath.com@rpl:devel//foresight.rpath.org@fl:1-devel//1/2.0.0.6-0.1-1
    group-dist=/foresight.rpath.org@fl:1-devel//1/1.3.2-0.7-3

References:
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2007-3844
    http://cve.mitre.org/cgi-bin/cvename.cgi?name=CVE-2007-3845

Description:
    Previous versions of the thunderbird package are vulnerable to a flaw in
    handling of "about:blank" windows. A malicious web server could exploit
    this to steal sensitive information or modify contents of other open web
    pages. 

    In addition, a malicious web server could execute helpers with arbitrary
    arguments due to thunderbird's mishandling of certain types of characters when
    launching external programs.

